<p pid="2">This video will help you understand Git commands from the ground up. It will explain commands in graphical representation with animations that will make it very easy to understand different Git commands. You will see how a Git tree is structured and how it works, how to branch and merge, and the difference between merge (non fast-forward) and rebase (fast-forward merge). You will also learn how to cherry pick, how to squash before merges, and much more.</p> 
